          "$type": "text",
          "text": "{\"week_number\":1,\"phase_type\":\"Base\",\"weekly_target_km\":15,\"is_deload_week\":false,\"sunday\":{\"slot_type\":\"Rest\",\"workout_type\":null,\"notes\":\"Full rest day. Let your body absorb the week ahead. Gentle walking or stretching is totally fine if you feel restless.\"},\"monday\":{\"slot_type\":\"Rest\",\"workout_type\":null,\"notes\":\"Second rest day to bookend your weekend. Recovery is where fitness is actually built — this is productive time.\"},\"tuesday\":{\"slot_type\":\"Run\",\"workout_type\":\"Easy\",\"notes\":\"Easy run, 5 km at 7:00–8:00/km. This should feel genuinely conversational — if you can't chat, slow down. Building your aerobic base starts here.\"},\"wednesday\":{\"slot_type\":\"Rest\",\"workout_type\":null,\"notes\":\"Rest day between your two midweek efforts. Your legs will thank you tomorrow.\"},\"thursday\":{\"slot_type\":\"Run\",\"workout_type\":\"Easy\",\"notes\":\"Easy run, 5 km at 7:00–8:00/km. Same feel as Tuesday — relaxed, comfortable, no heroics. Consistency over intensity at this stage.\"},\"friday\":{\"slot_type\":\"Rest\",\"workout_type\":null,\"notes\":\"Rest day before your long run. Light stretching or a short walk is fine, but save your legs for Saturday.\"},\"saturday\":{\"slot_type\":\"Run\",\"workout_type\":\"LongRun\",\"notes\":\"Long run, 5 km at 7:00–8:00/km. Your weekly anchor session. Keep it easy and steady — this is your aerobic foundation run. Enjoy the process.\"},\"week_summary\":\"Welcome to Week 1, Sarah! This opening week matches your current training load exactly — 15 km across three runs, all at easy effort. There's no ramp-up pressure here; the goal is simply to establish the rhythm of three running days per week and get comfortable with the structure. Every run this week is at easy pace (7:00–8:00/km), which builds your aerobic engine without overtaxing your body. Think of this as laying the foundation everything else will be built on. How does this structure feel given your current routine?\"}"
        }
